		"description": "<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; margin: 0.5em 0px; color: #191813; font-family: Signika, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Prerequisite: 7th level, Eldritch Whip feature</em></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; margin: 0.5em 0px; color: #191813; font-family: Signika, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">When you hit a creature with your Eldritch Whip, you can force it to make a Constitution saving throw or be paralyzed for 1 minute. At the end of each of its turns, the paralyzed creature can repeat the saving throw, ending the effect on a success.</span></p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text; margin: 0.5em 0px; color: #191813; font-family: Signika, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\"><span class=\"fontstyle1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Once you use this feature, you cannot do so again until you finish a short or long rest. You also regain the use of this feature after you&rsquo;ve spent 5 spell points to cast a spell or use other warlock features.</span></p>",
